cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving graph analytics using homomorphic encryption. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses how to encrypt and query graphs, which are common data structures in databases. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes running graph analytics on the cloud, which involves distributed computing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses how to perform graph analytics on encrypted graphs, which requires developing new algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses hard computation outsourcing, which involves analyzing the computational complexity of certain operations.
